{
  "article_id": "ReadingTimesAndDispatch1879",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "The ingenious web of fiction woven by De Foe into his \"Robinson Crusoe,\" is rivalled [sic] by the following story related and vouched for by the San Francisco Chronicle as true in every particular. Messrs. "
      },
      {
        "text": "George Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Charles Brown",
        "entity_key": "cdi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", both living, are named by the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Chronicle",
        "entity_key": "sfchronicle",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "as its authority for the appended narrative. In the spring of 1835, the small schooner \""
      },
      {
        "text": "[Peor es] Nada",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ",\" built at "
      },
      {
        "text": "Monterey",
        "entity_key": "ci_mo",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", was chartered by "
      },
      {
        "text": "Lewis T. Burton",
        "entity_key": "lbu",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Isaac J. Sparks",
        "entity_key": "isp",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "for an otter-hunting expedition from "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "to the coast of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Lower California",
        "entity_key": "re_baja",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". The trip proved unsuccessful and "
      },
      {
        "text": "the vessel",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "put into port at "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Pedro",
        "entity_key": "ci_sp",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Seventy miles southwest of "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Pedro",
        "entity_key": "ci_sp",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "from "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "is the small island of "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicholas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", which was then inhabited by "
      },
      {
        "text": "Indians",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The "
      },
      {
        "text": "\"Nara\" [Peor es Nada]",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "was dispatched by the authorities to remove them to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the mainland",
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "Nineteen men, women and children",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "were taken on board, and as "
      },
      {
        "text": "the vessel",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "was preparing to depart, "
      },
      {
        "text": "one of the Indian mothers",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "discovered that "
      },
      {
        "text": "two of her offspring",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "had been forgotten and left on "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "She sprang overboard and swam ashore in search of ",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the missing children",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", one of them three years old and the other an infant unable to walk.",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "The "
      },
      {
        "text": "[Peor es] Nada",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "for some unexplained reason sailed without "
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and "
      },
      {
        "text": "her children",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and never returned to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "The place",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "was not again visited until 1857 [1851], when "
      },
      {
        "text": "George Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", a hunter, stopped there for a few days. "
      },
      {
        "text": "He noticed three small circular inclosures almost a mile apart, the walls four feet high and a small opening on one side. Near these openings was a tripod of drift wood supporting dried seal blubber. He also saw a foot print which from its small size and arched center he judged to be that of a woman. He left ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "without seeing anyone. In 1852 ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Nidever",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "made a second trip at the request of ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Mission Fathers at Santa Barbara",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "jru",
          "aji",
          "sanchez",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "to make a careful search for ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the supposed lone inhabitant",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". He discovered a basket and clothing made of shag's skins, ropes of seal sinews, bone needles, etc, but before concluding the search, a heavy storm compelled him to seek a more hospitable harbor.",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "A third expedition, made to ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "in 1853, by ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Nidever",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Charles Brown",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "cdi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "four Indians",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "from the ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara Mission",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "mi_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", was more successful. On the day after landing, ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. Brown",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "cdi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "found ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the object of their search",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "at a distance, and cautiously approaching it from an opposite direction from ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the remainder of the party",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "col",
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", got quite closely [sic] to her without being observed. She was in one of her pens or wind-breaks, clothed in a garment made of the skins of the shag, without sleeves, low necked and, as observed when standing up, extending almost to the ankles. She was sitting cross-legged, skinning seal blubber with a rude knife made of a piece of hoop iron driven into a piece of wood. There was no covering on her head excepting a thick mass of matted hair of a yellowish brown color, due to the exposure to the sun and air. The hair was short[,] looking as though the free ends had rotted off. She would occasionally raise her hand and shade her eyes, and look toward ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the other men",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "col",
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "on a sandy plain near the beach, whom she evidently saw. ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "The balance of the party",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "col",
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "were now signaled in order that she might be captured if she attempted to escape.",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "To the surprise of all she made no attempt to get away, but greeted each one as they approached with a bow and a smile, and chattered all the time in a dialect that none of them understood, although ",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          3
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "accompanying ",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. Nidever",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "were acquainted with several Indian dialects.",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "She was talking apparently to herself from the time "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. Brown",
        "entity_key": "cdi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "approached in hearing distance until she was made aware of his presence. "
      },
      {
        "text": "The expression of her face was pleasant, her features were regular and her complexion much fairer and her form more symmetrical than that of the Indian women on the main land; and she is believed to have belonged to ",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a different and superior race",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "By signs and other means of communication, she was made aware that they wanted her to accompany them, and without any apparent hesitation she made ready to follow. In their course to where "
      },
      {
        "text": "the schooner",
        "entity_key": "sh_nidever",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "lay at anchor, they found a beautiful spring of water issuing from the bank above the beach, under a shelving rock."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The cracks or fissures in this rock were stuck full of bones, and there were other evidences of an encampment of ",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the lone inhabitant",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "of ",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". These bones were used for nourishment obtained by sucking; they were dried and resucked many times, showing that occasionally she was put upon short rations, but at the time of her discovery appeared to have an abundance, such as it was. She retained all her teeth, but they were worn low, supposed to be due to her chewing tough and solid articles of food. Her age appeared to be about 50 years. ",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. Brown",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ],
        "entity_key": "cdi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "made her a skirt of ticking, with which, and a sailor's cotton shirt and a black necktie, her dress was complete.",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "On arriving at ",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", she was taken to the "
      },
      {
        "text": "house of Mr. Nidever",
        "entity_key": "nideverhouse",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", where she became the center of attraction. "
      },
      {
        "text": "The Mission Fathers",
        "entity_keys": [
          "jru",
          "aji",
          "sanchez",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "took a great interest in her, sending to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Los Angeles",
        "entity_key": "ci_la",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and other places, hoping to find some one who could converse with her, but failed. Even the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Pepimaros Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_pepimaros",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who were said to have had an acquaintance with "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians on the island",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", could not understand her. "
      },
      {
        "text": "Two offers",
        "entity_key": "tru",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", one of $1000, for the privilege of taking her to "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Francisco",
        "entity_key": "ci_sf",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", were refused by "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". When found she was in excellent physical condition, strong and active, but the eating of fruit had [and] vegetable[s] brought on a sickness which, in connection with an injury to the spine received by falling from a porch, terminated her life four weeks later, or seven weeks from the time she landed. Her dress of shag skins, basket and trinkets were given to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Father Gonzalez",
        "entity_key": "jru",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Mission",
        "entity_key": "mi_santabarbaramission",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who, it is said, sent them to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Rome",
        "entity_key": "ci_rom",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ]
  ]
}